A 46-YEAR-OLD brigadier, based at the organised crime unit of the detective service head office and her 50-year-old husband, were expected to appear in the Pretoria Magistrates Court on Thursday, 10 December. This after they were arrested on Thursday morning for corruption and defeating the ends of justice. According to Hawks spokeswoman Colonel Katlego Mogale, the pair handed themselves over to the Directorate for Priority Crime Investigation team tasked with the investigation of criminal activities relating to Prophet Shepherd Bushiri. She said their warrants of arrest were authorised on Wednesday, 9 December in relation to an amount of R500 000 that was allegedly paid to the brigadier. “The investigation started as an inquiry and it was converted into a case docket in February 2020,” said Mogale.